Refactor: Split model repositories and support HF Hub IDs for all training stages

Previously all model checkpoints (SFT, Reward Model, GRPO) were uploaded
to sub-folders of a single HuggingFace Hub repository. This made version
management and downstream loading awkward. Each training stage now has its
own dedicated repository and uploads to the repository root. Loading logic
across all scripts now accepts Hub repo IDs in addition to local paths.

--- New Repository Layout ---

  MRBSTUDIO/Humor-Qwen3-8B-SFT      (was: humor-qwen3-8b/sft/)
  MRBSTUDIO/Humor-Reward-Model-1.7B  (was: humor-qwen3-8b/reward_model/)
  MRBSTUDIO/Humor-Qwen3-8B-GRPO      (was: humor-qwen3-8b/grpo/reward_model/)

All three repositories receive the full model folder at their root
(path_in_repo=""), rather than a named sub-folder.

--- Commit message convention ---

Commit messages follow the pattern "<stage>: <wandb_run_name>", e.g.:
  sft: sft-zh-v2
  reward_model: rm-balanced-v3
  grpo: grpo-rm-v1

This ties each HF commit to the corresponding Wandb experiment run for
straightforward cross-referencing during model comparison.

