--- HF Hub ID support for model loading ---

rl/reward_model.py
  Added _is_hub_repo(path) helper: returns True when path is not an
  existing local directory (i.e., it is a Hub repo ID string).

  _load_reward_model() updated:
    - Skips local Path.exists() check when loading from a Hub ID.
    - Uses huggingface_hub.file_exists() to detect adapter_config.json
      on the Hub (instead of local Path.exists()).
    - Uses hf_hub_download() to fetch adapter_config.json content when
      the source is a Hub ID.
    - Passes repo ID strings directly to PeftModel.from_pretrained()
      and AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(), which
      both natively resolve Hub IDs.

rl/train_grpo.py  –  load_sft_merged_model()
  Parameter renamed sft_adapter_path → sft_adapter_repo.
  Removed hard FileNotFoundError for non-existent local path (Hub IDs
  are not local paths).
  PeftModel.from_pretrained() now receives the Hub ID string directly,
  which it handles natively alongside local paths.

sft/eval_sft.py  –  load_sft_model() / run_benchmark_eval()
  PeftModel.from_pretrained() and the lm-eval peft= model_args string
  both accept Hub repo IDs without further modification.

